      • getTestStateByDerivedRequirementId

        public Map<String,TestState> getTestStateByDerivedRequirementId()
        Description copied from interface: AssessmentResultBuilder
        Retrieves the mapping of derived requirement identifiers to TestState. To be tested the derived requirement must: 1) have an associated TestResult provided by calling the AssessmentResultBuilder.addTestResult(Assessment, Document, String, TestResult) method, or 2) be declared as a specific TestState by calling the AssessmentResultBuilder.assignTestStatus(Assessment, Document, String, TestState) method.
        Specified by:
        getTestStateByDerivedRequirementId in interface AssessmentResultBuilder
        Returns:
        a map of derived requirement identifiers to the corresponding test status

      • start

        public AssessmentResultBuilder start()
        Description copied from interface: AssessmentResultBuilder
        Calling this method signals the start of the assessment. The assessment will be automatically started the first time either AssessmentResultBuilder.addTestResult(Assessment, Document, String, TestResult) or AssessmentResultBuilder.assignTestStatus(Assessment, Document, String, TestState) is called. Multiple calls to this method will not change the start time from the initial time.
        Specified by:
        start in interface AssessmentResultBuilder
        Returns:
        the same builder instance

      • assignTestStatus

        public <DOC extends Document> AssessmentResultBuilder assignTestStatus(Assessment<? extends DOC> assessment,
                                                                       DOC document,
                                                                       String derivedRequirementId,
                                                                       TestState state)
        Description copied from interface: AssessmentResultBuilder
        Marks the derived requirement associated with the provided identifier as having a specific TestState. This method is called when the AssessmentResultBuilder.addTestResult(Assessment, Document, String, TestResult) method is called. If no test result is reported for a given derived requirement, then this method needs to be called to indicate the actual test state of a derived requirement.
        Specified by:
        assignTestStatus in interface AssessmentResultBuilder
        Type Parameters:
        DOC - the type of document that is the target of the assessment
        Parameters:
        assessment - the target assessment
        document - the document being assessed
        derivedRequirementId - the derived requirement to set the state for
        state - the state to assign
        Returns:
        the current builder instance
